Distribution of data

The normality of the QA values was assessed using the shapiro-wilks test of normality. QA values from males was not normally distributed in the area left cingulum (p = 0.0221391) but normally distributed in the right cingulum (p=0.0896902), Left fornix (p=0.2152759), and Right Fornix (p = 0.2843453).


Table 1.p values from normality tests using shapiro-wilks.

Left cingulum Right cingulum Left Fornix Right Fornix
Males 0.0221391 0.0896902 0.2152759 0.2843453
